The paper deals with learning non-Markovian reward functions in Markov decision processes (MDPs), which is a problem in artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as active learning and optimization, which are covered in cs.LG and cs.DM. The paper also deals with the synchronization of a Mealy machine with an MDP, which falls under the category of control systems, covered in cs.SY. Finally, the paper involves software engineering techniques such as testing and implementation, which are covered in cs.SE.
